  "title": "Web Developer (Backend/ DevOps)",
  "description": "<p>Our esteemed client in the <strong>IT industry</strong> is seeking a <strong>Web Developer (focus on backend & devops) </strong>to join their dynamic team: </p><ul><li><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Permanent </li><li><strong>Position:</strong> Web Developer </li><li><strong>Location:</strong> MacPherson</li><li><strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday to Friday, 9.30am to 6.30pm</li><li><strong>Salary Package:</strong> Up to $7,000 + Bonus</li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Design, develop, and enhance secure and scalable backend systems for cloud-based\napplications.</li><li>Work closely with cross-functional teams in an agile and DevOps-focused environment\nto deliver reliable, high-quality software.</li><li>Build and maintain high-performance APIs and backend services within cloud-native\narchitectures.</li><li>Collaborate with DevOps teams to automate CI/CD workflows, monitoring, and infrastructure\nprovisioning.</li><li>Apply TDD practices, conduct code reviews, and follow established security standards.</li><li>Diagnose, troubleshoot, and optimize backend systems for performance, reliability, and\nobservability.</li><li>Contribute to system architecture aligned with security and regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Computer Science, IT, or a related field.</li><li>At least 4 years of practical experience with .NET Core, Node.js, or Ruby.</li><li>Familiar with Git workflows and CI/CD tools.</li><li>Skilled in RESTful APIs, GraphQL, and WebSockets.</li><li>Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud), containerization, and\ndatabases.</li><li>Understanding of monitoring and logging tools.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Ready to apply? Here’s how:</strong> </p><ul><li>Click the APPLY button, or </li><li>Email your resume (in MS Word or PDF format) to <a href=\"mailto:adelin@intuitrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">adelin@intuitrecruitment.com.</a> Include the job title in your email subject line for prompt processing. </li></ul><p><em><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></em><em> </em><br /><br />By submitting your application, you consent to the collection and use of your personal data\nunder Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA). </p><p><br />Adelin Chong | EA Personnel Reg No.: R1875641 </p><p>Intuit Recruitment Pte Ltd | EA License No.: 25C2793 </p>",
